F497D'>Currently, I want to know whether all functions in VPM, such as rule modification and layer management,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>can be managed through REST API.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Q2) Currently, it is not possible to reflect policies on Excel, and there are no plans to improve this function in the future. Is that correct?<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Regards,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-autospace:none;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><img width=624 height=227 id="ê·¸ë¦¼_x0020_1" src="cid:image007.jpg@01DBB2AC.A0080200" alt="ë°ëì_ìëª(2025)"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>From:</span></b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'> broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com [mailto:broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com] <br><b>Sent:</b> Thursday, April 17, 2025 6:49 PM<br><b>To:</b> dsp0701@etechsystem.co.kr; kevin@etechsystem.co.kr<br><b>Cc:</b> symantec-blue@etechsystem.co.kr; broadcomsupport.apac@westcon.com<br><b>Subject:</b> {Case#80026785} ##High - P2 - SAMSUNG ELECTRONICS CO,.LTD-Is management via API possible in WEB VPM?<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><div><div><p><span lang=EN-US>Hi Team,<br><br>Please refer below for my answer.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>(Q)I wonder if I can do all the actions currently managed through VPM when using Proxy through REST API.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>For example, is it possible to do detailed settings and Enable/Disable for the 100th Rule through API? I wonder if all management is possible through REST API even without using VPM.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>(A)-You can use this API if you want to access Management Center&nbsp;<strong><span style='font-family:êµ´ë¦¼'>without using the UI</span></strong> or want to trigger&nbsp;Management Center&nbsp;operation without using the UI. This REST&nbsp;API has the ability to:<o:p></o:p></span></p><div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-US>Access and raise alerts.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-US>View registered devices, device health, and other monitoring variables.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-US>View jobs and job execution status.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-US>Create, edit, schedule, and execute jobs.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-US>Show basic device information like version, disk usage, and name of device.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-US>Manage devices using the device CLI or device scripts.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:êµ´ë¦¼'>Manage policy, including creating new objects, changing the policy content, and installing policy on a device.</span></strong><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo1'><span lang=EN-US>Manage MC settings, and return system sensors and monitors.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div></div><p><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Please refer below KB for more information on REST API.<b><br><br><strong><span style='font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë"'><a href="https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/web-and-network-security/management-center/4-1/api.html" target=blank>Management Center REST&nbsp;API</a></span></strong><br><br></b>(Q)Additionally, you said that you can extract the policy into Excel. </span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Please tell me how to do that and also answer the question about whether it is impossible to insert the policy into Excel.</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>(A)-Currently ProxySG <strong><span style='font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë"'>do not support the option to export policy to excel format.</span></strong> If you noticed before, in the policy trace, the policy is structured as a line of command which is check one by one with MISS and MATCH status. As ProxySG are <strong><span style='font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë"'>built to use multiple layer</span></strong> like forwarding, authentication and access with different format and function, <strong><span style='font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë"'>it almost impossible to create a general rule which can fit into Excel row and column.</span></strong>&nbsp;<br><br></span><span lang=EN-US>-For exporting the policy to Excel format, <strong><span style='font-family:êµ´ë¦¼'>there already FR for this feature, but there is no plan to add this feature for now</span></strong>.<br><br>Regard,<br>Fauzee<o:p></o:p></span></p><div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-US><hr size=2 width="100%" align=center></span></div><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><div><div><p class=MsoNormal style='background:#FCF3CF'><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:red'>NOTE:</span></b><span lang=EN-US> </span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>This email was received from an external source. If there is anything suspicious or unusual about this email please <b><span style='color:red'>DO NOT</span></b> open any attachments or click any lin