ottom-alt:auto'><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>From:</span></strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'> broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com [mailto:broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com] <br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Sent:</span></strong> Monday, April 14, 2025 3:58 PM<br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>To:</span></strong> kevin@etechsystem.co.kr<br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Cc:</span></strong> symantec-blue@etechsystem.co.kr<br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Subject:</span></strong> {Case#80026785} ##High - P2 - SAMSUNG ELECTRONICS CO,.LTD-Is management via API possible in WEB VPM?</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US>Hi Jinyoung Hong,<br><br>Regarding your question please refer below for the answer:<br><br></span><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Q1) The existing Java VPM has changed to support WEB VPM.</span></strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif'><br><strong><span style='font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Is it possible to manage via API in WEB VPM?</span></strong></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>The ProxySG does not have APIs that fetch data from the ProxySG or integrate with third-party products.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>Workaround :&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>1. Use the Management Center REST API.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US><br>Management Center can connect to the ProxySG to apply changes.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>See the documen