0026785} ##High - P2 - SAMSUNG ELECTRONICS CO,.LTD-Is management via API possible in WEB VPM?</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US>Hi Jinyoung Hong,<br><br>Regarding your question please refer below for the answer:<br><br></span><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Q1) The existing Java VPM has changed to support WEB VPM.</span></strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif'><br><strong><span style='font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Is it possible to manage via API in WEB VPM?</span></strong></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>The ProxySG does not have APIs that fetch data from the ProxySG or integrate with third-party products.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>Workaround :&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>1. Use the Management Center REST API.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US><br>Management Center can connect to the ProxySG to apply changes.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>See the documentation on the REST API:&nbsp;<a href="https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/web-and-network-security/management-center/3-3/api.html" title="Management Center REST API">Management Center REST API</a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>2. The ProxySG has a number of read-only advanced URL like https://&lt;ProxySG_IP_address&gt;:8082/sysinfo or https://&lt;ProxySG_IP_address&gt;:8082/policy/&nbsp;<br><br>These are not APIs but the URLs can be used to fetch information about the proxy.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>3. The ProxySG's SSH interface