le='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>and I don't know if it is possible.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>The number of objects will be in the thousands to tens of thousands,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>and the number of rules will also be in the tens of thousands.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>So a careful answer is needed.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>All functions performed in VPM should be possible through REST API.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Regards,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-autospace:none;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";co