></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l14 level1 lfo6'><span lang=EN-US>Manage devices using the device CLI or device scripts.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo7'><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:êµ´ë¦¼'>Manage policy, including creating new objects, changing the policy content, and installing policy on a device.</span></strong><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div><div><ul type=disc><li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l12 level1 lfo8'><span lang=EN-US>Manage MC settings, and return system sensors and monitors.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul></div></div><p><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Please refer below KB for more information on REST API.<b><br><br><strong><span style='font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë"'><a href="https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/web-and-network-security/management-center/4-1/api.html">Management Center REST&nbsp;API</a></span></strong><br><br></b>(Q)Additionally, you said that you can extract the policy into Excel. </span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Please tell me how to do that and also answer the question about whether it is impossible to insert the policy into Excel.</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>(A)-Currently ProxySG <strong><span style='font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë"'>do not support the option to export policy to excel format.</span></strong> If you noticed before, in the policy trace, the policy is structured as a line of command which is check one by one with MISS and MATCH status. As Prox