><p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-autospace:none;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><img width=624 height=227 id="ê·¸ë¦¼_x0020_1" src="cid:image016.jpg@01DBB443.6E39C590" alt="ë°ëì_ìëª(2025)"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>From:</span></b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'> broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com [mailto:broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com] <br><b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, April 22, 2025 3:49 PM<br><b>To:</b> dsp0701@etechsystem.co.kr; kevin@etechsystem.co.kr<br><b>Cc:</b> symantec-blue@etechsystem.co.kr; broadcomsupport.apac@westcon.com<br><b>Subject:</b> {Case#80026785} ##High - P2 - SAMSUNG ELECTRONICS CO,.LTD-Is management via API possible in WEB VPM?<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><div><div><p><span lang=EN-US>Hi Team,<br><br>The way the REST API function is never meant to replace the VPM ease of use. User need to know all the syntax of the REST API function and additionally the syntax of the proxysg cpl line.&nbsp;<br><br>What you're looking for is policy manager to manage the policy without using web VPM like java based in previous version. And unfortunately this is not supported on web based console.<br><br>Please contact SE to raise feature request for this feature.&nbsp;<br><br>Regards,<br>Fauzee<o:p></o:p></span></p><div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-US><hr size=2 width="100%" align=center></span></div><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><div><div><p class=MsoNormal style='background:#FCF3CF'><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:red'>NOTE:</span></b><span lang=EN-US> </span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>This email was received from an external source. If there is anything suspicious or unusual about this email please <b><span style='color:red'>DO NOT</span></b> open any attachments or click any links and report the email using the Report Message button.</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><div><div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Hi, Team</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><img width=475 height=85 id="_x0000_i1026" src="cid:image002.jpg@01DBB443.6E313A10" alt=image.png></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Is VPM not possible in the Content Type section?</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>The customer is wondering if it is possible to manage or convert all functions including objects and rules currently used in VPM and automate them through API.</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>I think this is quite cumbersome and difficult,</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>and I don't know if it is possible.</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>The number of objects will be in the thousands to tens of thousands,</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><s