s-serif;color:red'>DO NOT</span></strong> open any attachments or click any links and report the email using the Report Message button.</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><div><div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>Hi, Team<br><br>Thank you for your support.<br><br>I was thinking the same thing about the contents, but I opened a case because of the customer's request. For now, I understand that both are impossible.<br>Q1) Are there any plans to support these in the future?<br>Q2) Aren't only simple tasks such as creating and modifying objects possible through REST API in MC? Can all the functions provided by VPM be managed through REST API?<br><br>Regards,</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-autospace:none;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'><img border=0 width=624 height=227 id="_x0000_i1037" src="cid:image013.jpg@01DBB443.6E313A10" alt=image.png></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;word-break:break-hangul'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"ë§ì ê³ ë";color:#1F497D'>&nbsp;</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>From:</span></strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'> broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com [mailto:broadcomsupport@apaccms.westcon.com] <br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Sent:</span></strong> Monday, April 14, 2025 3:58 PM<br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>To:</span></strong> kevin@etechsystem.co.kr<br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Cc:</span></strong> symantec-blue@etechsystem.co.kr<br><strong><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Subject:</span></strong> {Case#80026785} ##High - P2 - SAMSUNG ELECTRONICS CO,.LTD-Is management via API possible in WEB VPM?</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US>Hi Jinyoung Hong,<br><br>Regarding your question please refer below for the answer:<br><br></span><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Q1) The existing Java VPM has changed to support WEB VPM.</span></strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif'><br><strong><span style='font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Is it possible to manage via API in WEB VPM?</span></strong></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>The ProxySG does not have APIs that fetch data from the ProxySG or integrate with third-party products.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>Workaround :&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>1. Use the Management Center REST API.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US><br>Management Center can connect to the ProxySG to apply changes.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>See the documentation on the REST API:&nbsp;<a href="https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/web-and-network-security/management-center/3-3/api.html" title="Management Center REST API">Management Center REST API</a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>2. The ProxySG has a number of read-only advanced URL like https://&lt;ProxySG_IP_address&gt;:8082/sysinfo or https://&lt;ProxySG_IP_address&gt;:8082/policy/&nbsp;<br><br>These are not APIs but the URLs can be used to fetch information about the proxy.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>3. The ProxySG's SSH interface can be utilized to make changes in the proxy configuration using the CLI. Using SSH it is possible to script commands for automation.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span lang=EN-US>Refer to the CLI documentation:&nbsp;<a href="https://techdocs.broadcom.com/us/en/symantec-security-software/web-and-network-security/edge-swg/7-3/index2/_privileged.html">ProxySG Command Line Reference</a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US><a href="https://knowledge.broadcom.com/external/article/206621/proxysg-api-to-gather-data-and-integrate.html">ProxySG API to gather data and integrate with other reporting products</a><br><br></span><strong><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'>Q2) Can't the policy be reflected in Excel format instead of XML format in WEB VPM?</span></strong><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Poppins",serif;background:white'><br><br></span></b><span lang=EN-US>Currently ProxySG do not support the option to export policy to excel format. If you noticed before, in the policy trace, the policy is structured as a line of command which is check one by one with MISS and MATCH status. As ProxySG are built to use multiple layer like forwarding, authentication and access with different format and function, it almost impossible to create a general rule which can fit into Excel row and column.&nbsp;<br><br>Regards,<br>Fauzee<o:p></o:p></span></p></div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm'><img border=0 width=1 height=1 id="_x0000_i1038" src="cid:image014.jpg@01DBB443.6E313A10" alt=image.png></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm'><img border=0 width=1 height=1 id="_x0000_i1039" src="cid:image014.jpg@01DBB443.6E313A10" alt=image.png></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div></div></div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm'><img border=0 width=1 height=1 id="_x0000_i1040" src="cid:image014.jpg@01DBB443.6E313A10" alt=image.png></span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div></div></div><p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm'><img border=0 width=1 height=1 id="_x0000_i1041" src="cid:ima